  "text": "A parametric wavelength converter (PWC) [CITATION_1] is an alternative approach to wavelength conversion because multiple wavelengths, multiple channels, can be converted simultaneously. To define both the original wavelength, w λ , requiring conversion, and the new wavelength, w λ ′ , a continuous pump-wavelength, p λ , is set to",
